 says, you stay there. That was J. Hoskin the bandmaster, and he said, you stay there. Of course I'd been on a cello before a - at home you see. I'd been practicing a cello. And - my uncle was a bandmaster you see and he'd been staying with us for a - in 
the holiday, and - he started me on the cello. Because the cello was in the house you see. So - when - when I got the double bass I - he said, you stay where you are, so - I've been there ever since.
