\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7678773 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1794554\charrsid7551432 
Oh had the - a piano, harmonium. And there was violin, my father had a violin that was made be - he - him and another - and a - he and an officer in the depot made fiddles. Aye. And - they made - particular measurements off a Strad, they got that - mana
ged to get - to - some - somebody had a Strad, and they'd gone and - and measured it and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6359732 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1794554\charrsid7551432 To copy it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7678773 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1794554\charrsid7551432 Try and copied it you see. However - I got lessons on the fiddle - a man in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Shannock Place{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, that's the - Shannock Hall, what do they call it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6359732 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1794554\charrsid7551432 Next to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}St George's{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} church do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7678773 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1794554\charrsid7551432 Aye, there's - not - not - not so far long, it's a big caf\'e9
 now. There used to be a building there and - they were all let out to different people. Shannock Place anyway. And I - I got lessons from a - a m
an there, on the - on the violin but - he was - far too strict. Oh - and he was careless in a way you know, but - I practiced a good bit of instruments. And then my - my brother, he took up the piano. And then - he wanted to join a band and he - he - he -
 he went down to \endash 
 the Haven Silver, and he got a brass bass there. And he - he learned that. He - practiced on it, and then he - for to get experience he - he - he joined the - Grass Market Mission band, played with them and then they - ultimately joined t
he Ninth Royal Cotts band. That's the kilters regiment in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}East London Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. And - he took lessons from the bandmaster on the piano. And he played in the - the picture drome Easter Road. In the silent days. He played at the picture-drome. That was only at
 night of course, he was doing - he was doing his - he - he was doing his work during - during the day. He was watch - watch - watch repairing you see. And then of course he went away to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Australia{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. Well I was in the - I got into the band - 1905 I think it was.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6359732 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1794554\charrsid7551432 You didn't actually have a double bass at home at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7678773 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1794554\charrsid7551432 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6359732 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1794554\charrsid7551432 It was kept with the band was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7678773 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1794554\charrsid7551432 Kept with the band, they'd two double basses you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6359732 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1794554\charrsid7551432 And if you wanted to practice it did that mean you had to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7678773 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1794554\charrsid7551432 
I - I carried - I carried - I carried it home. And - practiced twice a week. Tuesdays and Fridays, half past nine to eleven. And you was on duty in the mornings sometimes at five o'clock. For your work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6359732 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1794554\charrsid7551432 You must have enjoyed playing it then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7678773 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1794554\charrsid7551432 Y
es. Oh I was quite - quite enthusiastic. And then of course the bandmaster, he was bandmaster of the - \{BLANK\}
 at the military band you see. And - at - at that time - he had - they - he had only a band of - his - his regulation now was only twenty-one I th
ink it is, or - it's eighteen or twenty-one, something like that, a small band you see, for the Yeomanry. That's all they're allowed by the - by the Army authorities you see. But for taking engagements side they had to - augment his band, well he - he too
k five of us from the postal band, and we got uniforms and we played out for - engagements you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6359732 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1794554\charrsid7551432 Would you get paid for doing that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7678773 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1794554\charrsid7551432 Oh yes, aye, got paid for that, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6359732 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1794554\charrsid7551432 What about the Post band?
