st Office band, oh no. But they paid - we paid - when I was learning - paid a shilling a week - for lessons, like, that was for the bandmaster you see. A shilling a week. And then when you got into the band it was only - the - the - subscription was sixpe
nce a week. That paid - helped to pay up the uniform, of course we - we got the - got the practice room free.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6359732 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1794554\charrsid7551432 And your uniform was supplied by the band?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7678773 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1794554\charrsid7551432 Was supplied by the band, the band fund you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6359732 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1794554\charrsid7551432 You were in a choir, was anybody else in a choir in hour family?
