he army, he played the clarinet but he - he didn't play it - he didna play the clarinet at home. He learned it while in - in - in the Army. Oh we used to - all Sunday, go - go right through the hymn book. Aye, hymn book, through the hymn book. And then th
e
re was a chap lived up the street a bit, a cornet player, he - he tried to form a wee orchestra, we used to go up there to his house, we used to have a musical night, a musical evening so of course there was - there wasn't so many cinemas in those days yo
u see. Or - or theatres or - the - say - there was - aye, there was - ah there was cinemas right enough, there was - but there wasna very many.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6359732 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1794554\charrsid7551432 There was the Diarama that you spoke about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7678773 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1794554\charrsid7551432 Aye, the Diarama, it's closed, Diarama.
