Shift, aye, different shifts, aye. Eight - eight 'toil four. Nine - nine - nine 'til - nine 'til six. Nine 'til - nine 'til five and - I think the - you had to finish before nine o'clock at night. You finished at nine o'clock at night, that was the last.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6359732 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1794554\charrsid7551432 What about Saturdays and Sundays, what happened then?
