ou see, were - I was - my - my - after - assistant postman, before you - you're appointed assistant postman, and then - before you got your appointment you see, as a postman you see for Civil Service position, the - the men coming back from the Army were 
g
et - were - they were allowed more of them than messengers you see. And some of the messengers - had to go to the country - like - on a - I know one - I know - I know one chap went to - West Calder and - another one went to Mid Calder as postmen before th
ey got into - and then they - about two or three years and then they'd come back into Edinburgh.
