y week you see. And then - when I got into the other band - I was practice - band practice Monday, with the yeomanry, Tuesday with the post office, Wednesday with the yeomanry - Friday with the post office band, so - I'd only Thursday and Saturday - and S
u
nday free you see. And then - on Thursdays I - I got in with a - a chap - that was in the band, he played the oboe and he got into an amateur orchestra, St Andrews Amateur, still exists, aye, well the - there's a lady stays out here, she was a member of i
